The paper focuses on recommender systems, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of neural networks and convolutional neural networks also suggests a focus on deep learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with modeling user-item interactions, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of embeddings and correlations between dimensions suggests a focus on representation learning, which is also relevant to computer vision (cs.CV).
